section.t:
Suppose a bidirectional channel exists between the nodes A and B. The objective is to measure at A one or more of the following quantities associated with the channel: The one-way delay associated with the forward (A to B) direction of the channel;
The one-way delay associated with the reverse (B to A) direction of the channel;
The two-way delay (A to B to A) associated with the channel.

When an implementation supports only one timestamp format, the
            procedures above reduce to the following simple behavior:

                All DM Queries are transmitted with the same QTF;
                All DM Responses are transmitted with the same RTF, and the
                RPTF is always set equal to the RTF;
                All DM Responses received with RTF not equal to QTF are
                discarded;
                On a unidirectional channel, all DM Queries received
                with QTF not equal to the supported format are discarded.
